<section class="tb-tool-layout" data-controller="heic dropzone" data-action="dragover@window->dropzone#over dragleave@window->dropzone#leave drop@window->heic#drop">
  <div>
    <div class="tb-eyebrow">Tool 01</div>
    <h1 class="tb-h1 tb-tool-title">HEIC → JPG</h1>
    <p class="tb-text tb-tool-subtitle" style="max-width: 56ch;">
      Drop a pile of iPhone HEIC photos. We'll convert them to JPG, PNG or WebP right here
      in your browser. Nothing leaves your device.
    </p>

    <div class="tb-drop"
         data-heic-target="drop"
         data-dropzone-target="zone"
         data-action="click->heic#pick dragover->dropzone#over dragleave->dropzone#leave drop->heic#drop"
         style="margin-top: 26px;">
      <svg class="tb-drop-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/>
        <path d="M17 8l-5-5-5 5"/>
        <path d="M12 3v12"/>
      </svg>
      <div class="tb-drop-title">Drop HEIC photos here, or click to choose</div>
      <div class="tb-drop-sub">.heic · .heif · any number of files · 0 bytes uploaded</div>
    </div>

    <input type="file" accept="image/heic,image/heif,.heic,.heif" multiple
           data-heic-target="input" data-action="change->heic#picked" hidden>

    <div data-heic-target="options" hidden style="margin-top: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <div>
        <div class="tb-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 6px;">Quality</div>
        <div class="tb-tabs" data-heic-target="quality">
          <button class="tb-tab" data-action="click->heic#setQuality" data-q="0.8">80</button>
          <button class="tb-tab is-active" data-action="click->heic#setQuality" data-q="0.9">90</button>
          <button class="tb-tab" data-action="click->heic#setQuality" data-q="1.0">100</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="tb-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 6px;">Format</div>
        <div class="tb-tabs" data-heic-target="format">
          <button class="tb-tab is-active" data-action="click->heic#setFormat" data-f="image/jpeg">JPG</button>
          <button class="tb-tab" data-action="click->heic#setFormat" data-f="image/png">PNG</button>
          <button class="tb-tab" data-action="click->heic#setFormat" data-f="image/webp">WebP</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <span style="flex: 1;"></span>

      <button class="tb-btn tb-btn-quiet" data-action="click->heic#clear">Clear</button>
      <button class="tb-btn tb-btn-primary" data-action="click->heic#downloadZip" data-heic-target="zipBtn" disabled>
        Download all as .zip
      </button>
    </div>

    <div data-heic-target="list" class="tb-card" style="margin-top: 18px; display: none;"></div>
  </div>

  <aside>
    <div class="tb-receipt">
      <div class="tb-receipt-title">
        <span class="tb-receipt-dot"></span>
        <span>Live receipt</span>
      </div>
      <div class="tb-stack-6">
        <div class="tb-receipt-row is-good"><span>bytes sent</span><span data-receipt-target="bytes" data-heic-target="bytesSent">0</span></div>
        <div class="tb-receipt-row is-good"><span>bytes received</span><span>0</span></div>
        <div class="tb-receipt-row"><span>worker</span><span>heic2any</span></div>
        <div class="tb-receipt-row"><span>threads</span><span data-heic-target="threads">1</span></div>
        <div class="tb-receipt-row"><span>files queued</span><span data-heic-target="queued">0</span></div>
        <div class="tb-receipt-row"><span>files done</span><span data-heic-target="done">0</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="tb-receipt-foot">
        Open your browser DevTools. Watch the Network tab as you convert.
        Zero requests to our origin. Verifiable.
      </div>
    </div>
  </aside>
</section>

<section class="tb-seo">
  <h2>How do I convert HEIC to JPG?</h2>
  <p>
    Drop any number of HEIC files onto the box above (or tap it on your phone to pick from your camera roll).
    Each file is decoded locally in your browser using <span class="tb-mono">libheif</span> compiled to WebAssembly,
    then re-encoded as JPG, PNG or WebP at the quality you pick. No upload step, no progress bar for "sending to
    server" — just your CPU.
  </p>
  <h3>Why do iPhones save photos as HEIC?</h3>
  <p>
    HEIC (High Efficiency Image Container) gives photos that are roughly half the size of the equivalent JPG
    with no visible quality loss. Great for Apple devices. Not great for Windows, Android, older CMSes, or the
    friend you're trying to share a vacation album with.
  </p>
  <h3>Does this upload my photos?</h3>
  <p>
    No. The receipt card on this page reads your browser's resource timing API live. If this page makes a
    network request back to us while converting, that counter ticks up. Try it yourself with DevTools open.
  </p>
</section>
